The paper introduces a novel neural network model for question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The model is designed to enhance neural networks' ability to represent and calculate information over a long period by keeping records of entities contained in text. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in the arXiv CS repository, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Among these, cs.CL is the most likely category as it specifically deals with NLP tasks. The other categories are also relevant as they involve machine learning and neural networks, which are key components of the proposed model.
